@inproceedings{herzberg:2012,
	Abstract = {Process models gained more and more significance to carry out an
organization's operations. Besides documentation purposes, organizations strive
to evaluate their executed processes in terms of performance and conformance. However,
this is far from trivial: As most processes are still carried out manually, only
few effects can be tracked and are typically not related to process instances.

In this paper, we propose an architecture that defines event monitoring points:
Elementary state transitions of a process instance that are bound to a
configuration to discover events from a process agnostic technical environment.
We discuss applications of this architecture, towards monitoring, performance
measurement, and execution conformance.},
